{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Pastry","content":["Place flour, salt and thyme leaves  in mixing bowl then chop <b>10 sec\/speed 8<b>.","Add butter and water then mix <b>Turbo\/2 sec\/3-4 times<b> until just clinging together. Tip out and form into a ball. Divide into two equal pieces and wrap each in cling film and place in fridge to rest for 30-45 minutes. Meanwhile, make filling."]},{"title":"Filling","content":["Grease two large baking trays then set aside.","Place onions and oil in mixing bowl then chop <b>4 sec\/speed 4<b>.","Add red peppers, courgettes, salt and pepper then cook <b>5 min\/120°C\/\/speed <b>. Drain through a sieve to remove juices then set aside.","Preheat oven to 200°C. Fry sausages in a frying pan over a high heat, turning until browned on all sides. Remove and cut into bite-sized pieces then set aside.","On a lightly floured surface, roll each piece of pastry out into a circle (Ø 30 cm). Transfer each to a baking tray. Arrange half the vegetables over the top of each pastry disc, leaving a 5 cm border around the edge then arrange sausage pieces over vegetable layer.","Fold edges of pastry up around filling then brush crust with milk. Bake for 30-40 minutes (200°C) until pastry is cooked. Serve warm, cut in slices."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Pastry","content":["440 g plain flour, plus extra for rolling","¾ tsp fine sea salt","2 tsp fresh thyme leaves","220 g butter, diced, plus extra for greasing","70 - 100 g water"]},{"title":"Filling","content":["400 - 500 g red onions, quartered","30 g olive oil","350 - 400 g red peppers, cut in strips (5 mm)","350 - 400 g courgettes, cut in strips (5 mm)","1 tsp fine sea salt","½ tsp ground black pepper","400 g sausages, raw","1 Tbsp milk"]}],"id":"r87443","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-vfH0ZAwAOHA\/XZQvlo5TsrI\/AAAAAAAAcdg\/kOnThNrNNJw1VUqGK3DvYSKYe6-NNuCfwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_IUcSaeSTQ8_uscXW.png","title":"Pepper, Onion and Sausage Galettes","publishedAt":"2015-11-16T